# AnalyticsOps Normalized Data Model — V2 Schema Specification

**Schema:** `dbo`  
**Author:** Distinguished Engineering / Data Modeling Review  
**Date:** April 15, 2026  
**Status:** Proposed  
**Replaces:** All `Direct_Report.*` tables in `CRDP_DEV_MIRROR`

-----

## Executive Summary

The current reporting layer consists of 18+ `Direct_Report.*` tables built by pre-joining MongoDB extracts (`RawP.*`) with enterprise employee and org data. This approach stamped the full organizational hierarchy (Level 03–06, cost center, international/domestic flag, address columns) onto every table independently — creating 60+ redundant columns across the model and making maintenance, governance, and Power BI modeling unnecessarily complex.

This specification defines a normalized star schema of **10 tables** under `dbo` that eliminates all duplication, establishes a single source of truth for each business entity, and supports all five reporting domains: Adoption, Workload, Performance, Reliability, and Governance.

-----

## Design Principles

|Principle                            |Implementation                                                                                          |
|-------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|**Single source of truth**           |Each business entity (employee, application, collection, schedule) exists in exactly one dimension table|
|**Atomic grain**                     |`Fact_Job_Execution` stores one row per job — all aggregations computed in the BI layer                 |
|**No baked-in hierarchy duplication**|Org hierarchy lives only in `Dim_Employee`; facts carry a foreign key, not 15 repeated columns          |
|**Duration in seconds**              |All time-based measures stored as INT seconds; formatted (H:MM:SS) at the DAX/display layer             |
|**Surrogate keys**                   |Every dimension has an `_Id` (INT IDENTITY) surrogate key for join performance                          |
|**Natural keys preserved**           |Original business keys retained with source-qualified names to avoid collision with surrogates          |
|**Consistent naming**                |Pascal_Snake convention throughout; prefixes: `Dim_`, `Fact_`, `Bridge_`                                |
|**Flag convention**                  |All boolean columns use `[Noun]_Flag` (BIT) — e.g., `Error_Flag`, `Weekend_Flag`                        |
|**Computed flags at source**         |SLA breach flags computed during ETL (top 10% population stats), not at query time                      |

