## Table 10: Fact_Job_Execution

**Purpose:** The single atomic fact table for all Alteryx Server job executions. One row per job run. Replaces seven Direct_Report tables by joining `AS_Queue` (the queue/completion record) with `AS_Results` (the engine execution record) at the `AS_Queue_ID` grain, then resolving all dimension FKs via surrogate keys instead of denormalized columns. SLA breach flags are computed during ETL based on monthly population statistics (top 10% of runtimes).

**Source:** `RawP.AlteryxService_AS_Queue` + `RawP.AlteryxService_AS_Results` (joined on `AS_Queue_ID`) + breach computation logic

|Column                  |Data Type    |Nullable|Notes                                                                                                                               |
|------------------------|-------------|--------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|                        |             |        |**Keys & Foreign Keys**                                                                                                             |
|`Job_Execution_Id`      |INT IDENTITY |NO      |Surrogate key.                                                                                                                      |
|`Job_Id`                |VARCHAR(50)  |NO      |Natural key. `AS_Queue._id`.                                                                                                        |
|`Application_Id`        |INT          |NO      |FK to `Dim_Application`. Resolved from `AS_Queue.AS_Application_ID` → `Dim_Application.Service_Id`.                                 |
|`Employee_Id`           |INT          |YES     |FK to `Dim_Employee`. Resolved from `AS_Queue.UserName` → `AG_users` → `Dim_Employee`. NULL for anonymous runs.                     |
|`Schedule_Id`           |INT          |YES     |FK to `Dim_Schedule`. Resolved from `AS_Queue.AS_Schedules_ID`. NULL for ad-hoc (manual/API) runs.                                  |
|`Queue_Date_Id`         |INT          |NO      |FK to `Dim_Date`. Date portion of `Queue_Created_Dt`. Enables date-based slicing without timestamp parsing.                         |
|`Completion_Date_Id`    |INT          |YES     |FK to `Dim_Date`. Date portion of `Completion_Dt`. NULL if job hasn’t completed.                                                    |
|                        |             |        |**Timestamps**                                                                                                                      |
|`Queue_Created_Dt`      |DATETIME2(0) |NO      |When the job entered the queue. Source: `AS_Queue.CreationDateTime`.                                                                |
|`Engine_Start_Dt`       |DATETIME2(0) |YES     |When the engine began executing. Source: `AS_Results.ExecutionStartTime`. NULL if job never started.                                |
|`Completion_Dt`         |DATETIME2(0) |YES     |When the job finished. Source: `AS_Queue.CompletionDateTime`. NULL if still running or queued.                                      |
|                        |             |        |**Durations (all INT, in seconds)**                                                                                                 |
|`Queue_Wait_Seconds`    |INT          |YES     |Time spent waiting in queue before engine pickup. Pre-computed: `Engine_Start_Dt` − `Queue_Created_Dt`. Source column: `QUEUE_TIME`.|
|`Engine_Runtime_Seconds`|INT          |YES     |Engine execution time. Source: `AS_Results.ExecutionTime` (converted to seconds if stored as decimal).                              |
|`Total_Duration_Seconds`|INT          |YES     |End-to-end: `Completion_Dt` − `Queue_Created_Dt`. Equals `Queue_Wait_Seconds` + `Engine_Runtime_Seconds`.                           |
|                        |             |        |**Status & Outcome**                                                                                                                |
|`Execution_Status`      |VARCHAR(20)  |NO      |Current job state: ‘Queued’, ‘Running’, ‘Complete’. Source: `AS_Queue.Status`.                                                      |
|`Result_Code`           |TINYINT      |YES     |Engine result: 0 = Success, 1 = Warning, 2 = Error. Source: `AS_Queue.AlteryxResultCode`. NULL if not yet complete.                 |
|`Error_Flag`            |BIT          |NO      |1 when `Result_Code` = 2. Simplifies error rate calculations. Default 0.                                                            |
|`Warning_Flag`          |BIT          |NO      |1 when `Result_Code` = 1. Default 0.                                                                                                |
|`Error_Message`         |VARCHAR(2000)|YES     |Error text. Source: `AS_Queue.Error`. NULL on success.                                                                              |
|                        |             |        |**Execution Context**                                                                                                               |
|`Client_Type`           |VARCHAR(50)  |YES     |How the job was triggered: ‘Designer’, ‘Scheduler’, ‘API’, ‘Manual’. Source: `AS_Queue.ClientType`.                                 |
|`Worker_Tag`            |VARCHAR(50)  |YES     |Worker affinity tag. Relevant for multi-worker routing analysis.                                                                    |
|`Server_Id`             |VARCHAR(100) |YES     |Hostname + worker ID that executed the job. Source: `AS_Queue.Owner`.                                                               |
|`Priority`              |TINYINT      |YES     |Job execution priority. Source: `AS_Queue.QOS_Priority`.                                                                            |
|`Amp_Flag`              |BIT          |NO      |1 = executed with AMP (E2) engine. Source: `AS_Queue.RunWithE2`. Default 0.                                                         |
|`Anonymous_Flag`        |BIT          |NO      |1 = triggered by anonymous user. Source: `AS_Queue.IsAnonymous`. Default 0.                                                         |
|`Job_Name`              |VARCHAR(255) |YES     |For scheduled jobs: schedule name. For manual: user-assigned name. Source: `AS_Queue.JobName`.                                      |
|                        |             |        |**SLA Breach Flags**                                                                                                                |
|`Breach_Half_Hour_Flag` |BIT          |NO      |1 = runtime exceeded 30-minute threshold. Computed from population P90 statistics. Default 0.                                       |
|`Breach_Hour_Flag`      |BIT          |NO      |1 = runtime exceeded 60-minute threshold. Computed from population P90 statistics. Default 0.                                       |
|`Breach_Normal_Flag`    |BIT          |NO      |1 = runtime in top 10% of monthly population (above baseline). Computed during ETL. Default 0.                                      |
|`Peak_Window_Flag`      |BIT          |NO      |1 = job ran during 8:00–10:00 AM window. Supports resource contention analysis. Computed from `Queue_Created_Dt` hour. Default 0.   |
|                        |             |        |**Output Metadata**                                                                                                                 |
|`Result_File_Size_Bytes`|BIGINT       |YES     |Total output file size. Source: `AS_Results.TotalFileSize`. NULL if no output.                                                      |

