**Note on Bridge tables:** `Bridge_Collection_Access.Member_Id` is a polymorphic FK — it points to `Dim_Employee` when `Member_Type = 'User'` and `Dim_User_Group` when `Member_Type = 'Group'`. In Power BI, this requires two relationships (one active, one inactive) with DAX `USERELATIONSHIP()` for group-based filtering.

